<subSubSection box="[189,583,228,255]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,158,933]" box="[189,583,228,255]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,583,228,255]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">
Tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Salm-Dyck" authorityName="Salm-Dyck" box="[266,578,228,255]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Phyllocacteae">Phyllocacteae Salm-Dyck</taxonomicName>
:
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="88" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,158,933]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">
— 
<bibRefCitation author="Nyffeler, R. &amp; Eggli, U." box="[611,899,229,255]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" pagination="109 - 149" refId="ref18353" refString="Nyffeler, R. &amp; Eggli, U. (2010) A farewell to dated ideas and concepts: molecular phylogenetics and a revised suprageneric classification of the family Cactaceae. Schumannia 6: 109 - 149." type="journal article" year="2010">Nyffeler &amp; Eggli (2010)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the monophyly of the tribe is well supported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nyffeler, R." box="[288,464,264,290]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" pagination="312 - 326" refId="ref18317" refString="Nyffeler, R. (2002) Phylogenetic relationships in the Cactus family. American Journal of Botany 89: 312 - 326. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 89.2.312" type="journal article" year="2002">Nyffeler (2002)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Crozier, B. S." box="[517,686,264,291]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" refId="ref16333" refString="Crozier, B. S. (2005) Systematics of Cactaceae Juss.: phylogeny cpDNA evolution and classification, with emphasis on the genus Mammilaria Haw. Dissertation, The University of Texas at Austin, 154 pp." type="book" year="2005">Crozier (2005)</bibRefCitation>
. Moreover, for nomenclatural reasons, the name 
<taxonomicName box="[1231,1387,264,290]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Phyllocacteae">Phyllocacteae</taxonomicName>
(incl. Echinocereeae Buxb.) must be used because it has priority over all the other relevant tribal names, i.e. 
<taxonomicName authority="Buxb." authorityName="Buxb." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Hylocereeae">Hylocereeae Buxb.</taxonomicName>
, Leptocereeae Buxb., 
<taxonomicName authority="Buxb." authorityName="Buxb." box="[473,706,334,360]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Pachycereeae">Pachycereeae Buxb.</taxonomicName>
and Peniocereeae Doweld. Despite of this, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hunt, D. &amp; Taylor, N. &amp; Charles, G." box="[1234,1451,334,361]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" refId="ref17187" refString="Hunt, D., Taylor, N. &amp; Charles, G. (2013) The New Cactus Lexicon, Atlas of Illustrations. Dh Books, Milborn Port, 373 pp." type="book" year="2013">
Hunt 
<emphasis box="[1302,1364,334,360]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
placed the three Chilean genera (
<taxonomicName authority="Britton &amp; Rose" authorityName="Britton &amp; Rose" box="[517,847,369,396]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Austrocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[517,662,370,396]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Austrocactus</emphasis>
Britton &amp; Rose
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Phil., and Corryocactus Britton &amp; Rose" authorityName="Phil., and Corryocactus Britton &amp; Rose" box="[863,1444,369,396]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Eulychnia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[863,977,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Eulychnia</emphasis>
Phil., and 
<emphasis box="[1105,1257,370,396]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Corryocactus</emphasis>
Britton &amp; Rose
</taxonomicName>
) within Echinocereeae Buxb., 
<bibRefCitation author="Nyffeler, R. &amp; Eggli, U." box="[467,740,405,431]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" pagination="109 - 149" refId="ref18353" refString="Nyffeler, R. &amp; Eggli, U. (2010) A farewell to dated ideas and concepts: molecular phylogenetics and a revised suprageneric classification of the family Cactaceae. Schumannia 6: 109 - 149." type="journal article" year="2010">Nyffeler &amp; Eggli (2010)</bibRefCitation>
proposed the following three subtribes, one of which (Subtribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Buxb." authorityName="Buxb." box="[136,387,440,467]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Corryocactinae">Corryocactinae Buxb.</taxonomicName>
) includes the three Chilean genera. The relationships between 
<taxonomicName box="[1118,1263,440,466]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Austrocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1118,1263,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Austrocactus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1280,1394,440,466]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Eulychnia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1280,1394,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Eulychnia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[136,288,475,501]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Corryocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,288,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Corryocactus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was corroborated by various molecular-based studies (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nyffeler, R." box="[961,1123,475,501]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" pagination="312 - 326" refId="ref18317" refString="Nyffeler, R. (2002) Phylogenetic relationships in the Cactus family. American Journal of Botany 89: 312 - 326. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 89.2.312" type="journal article" year="2002">Nyffeler 2002</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hernandez-Hernandez, T. &amp; Hernandez, H. M. &amp; De-Nova, J. A. &amp; Puente, R. &amp; Eguiarte, L. E. &amp; Magallon, S." pageId="9" pageNumber="88" pagination="44 - 61" refId="ref16906" refString="Hernandez-Hernandez, T., Hernandez, H. M., De-Nova, J. A., Puente, R., Eguiarte, L. E. &amp; Magallon, S. (2011) Phylogenetic relationships and evolution of growth form in Cactaceae (Caryophyllales, Eudicotyledoneae). American Journal of Botany 98: 44 - 61. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 12066" type="journal article" year="2011">
Hernández-Hernández 
<emphasis box="[1394,1452,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
, Bárcenas 
<emphasis box="[315,371,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">et al.</emphasis>
2011).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
